## Phase 1: Code Hygiene (~ 1 week)

**Goal**: Eliminate all dead code, fix broken service paths, achieve a clean codebase.

### Tasks

| # | Task | Priority | Est. Time |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1.1 | **Delete `multiplayer/` and `collaboration/` from Codemaster Odyssey package** | 🔴 Critical | 1 hour |
| 1.2 | **Delete orphaned files**: [relay_game_screen.dart](file:///d:/Games/VERASSO/lib/features/learning/presentation/classroom/relay_game_screen.dart), [relay_game_service.dart](file:///d:/Games/VERASSO/lib/features/learning/presentation/classroom/services/relay_game_service.dart), example auth screens | 🔴 Critical | 1 hour |
| 1.3 | **Delete `lib/core/mesh/` directory** entirely (models + transports are all stubs) | 🟠 High | 30 min |
| 1.4 | **Remove `lib/error.txt`** from source | 🟡 Low | 5 min |
| 1.5 | **Fix `BackgroundSyncManager`**: Remove mesh listener, implement real Supabase sync for pending `OfflineStorageService` actions | 🔴 Critical | 1 day |
| 1.6 | **Refactor `learning_dashboard.dart`** (22KB) — extract into smaller widgets | 🟡 Medium | 1 day |
| 1.7 | **Clean up stubbed providers in `main.dart`**: Remove imports for `mesh_power_manager`, `mesh_sync_manager`, `sync_bridge_service` | 🟠 High | 1 hour |

### Exit Criteria
- [ ] `flutter analyze` passes with 0 issues
- [ ] No file in the project references "mesh" in active code paths
- [ ] Offline action queue actually syncs to Supabase when network is restored

---

## Phase 2: Critical Testing (~2 weeks)

**Goal**: Achieve minimum 60% test coverage on auth, gamification, and core game mechanics.

### Tasks

| # | Task | Priority | Est. Time |
|---|---|---|---|
| 2.1 | **Auth unit tests**: Sign in, sign up, sign out, MFA enrollment, MFA verification, OTP, password validation, cooldown logic | 🔴 Critical | 4 days |
| 2.2 | **Auth integration tests**: Full login flow, OAuth redirect, biometric fallback, session refresh | 🔴 Critical | 2 days |
| 2.3 | **Gamification unit tests**: XP calculation, badge requirements, tier progression, streak calculation, leaderboard | 🟠 High | 3 days |
| 2.4 | **Fix existing Codemaster Odyssey tests**: Run all 11 tests, fix failures from `google_fonts` removal and single-player conversion | 🟠 High | 2 days |
| 2.5 | **Core service tests**: `OfflineStorageService` queue/dequeue, `NetworkConnectivityService` status changes, `ContentRecommendationService` | 🟠 High | 3 days |
| 2.6 | **Social feature smoke tests**: Feed loading, post creation, comment submission | 🟡 Medium | 2 days |

### Exit Criteria
- [ ] `flutter test` passes with 0 failures
- [ ] Auth flows have >80% branch coverage
- [ ] Every Supabase RPC call is tested with mock responses
- [ ] Codemaster Odyssey's 11 existing tests all pass

---

## Phase 3: Security Verification (~1.5 weeks)

**Goal**: Validate that the security architecture actually works, not just compiles.

### Tasks

| # | Task | Priority | Est. Time |
|---|---|---|---|
| 3.1 | **Test `EncryptionService`**: Verify AES-GCM encrypt/decrypt roundtrip, key derivation, Hive key generation | 🔴 Critical | 1 day |
| 3.2 | **Test `InputValidator`**: Fuzz test all 10KB of validation rules with malicious inputs (XSS, SQL injection, Unicode exploits) | 🔴 Critical | 2 days |
| 3.3 | **Deploy `rate-limiter` edge function** and verify it blocks brute-force auth attempts | 🔴 Critical | 1 day |
| 3.4 | **Add server-side password policy** via Supabase Auth config (minimum length, complexity) | 🟠 High | 2 hours |
| 3.5 | **Verify RLS policies**: Write integration tests that attempt unauthorized data access and confirm it's blocked | 🔴 Critical | 2 days |
| 3.6 | **Test `SessionTimeoutService`**: Verify auto-logout on idle, session refresh, screen lock trigger | 🟡 Medium | 1 day |
| 3.7 | **Certificate pinning verification**: Confirm `PinnedHttpClient` is actually used by the Supabase client (it likely isn't — Supabase Flutter SDK manages its own HTTP client) | 🟠 High | 4 hours |

### Exit Criteria
- [ ] All security services have unit tests
- [ ] Rate limiting is active on auth endpoints
- [ ] RLS policies block cross-user data access
- [ ] Encryption roundtrip is verified

---

## Phase 4: CI/CD Hardening (~1 week)

**Goal**: Reliable, automated build and deployment pipeline.

### Tasks

| # | Task | Priority | Est. Time |
|---|---|---|---|
| 4.1 | **Fix GitHub Actions secrets**: Add all required secrets (`SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, `SENTRY_DSN`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, etc.) to the repository | 🔴 Critical | 1 hour |
| 4.2 | **Fix Android build on CI**: Verify Gradle config works on Linux (CI) where drive mismatch doesn't apply | 🟠 High | 2 hours |
| 4.3 | **Deploy all 5 edge functions** to Supabase production | 🔴 Critical | 1 day |
| 4.4 | **Run `999_verify_deployment.sql`** against production Supabase to confirm all tables, RPCs, and triggers exist | 🔴 Critical | 2 hours |
| 4.5 | **Set up staging environment**: Create a Supabase staging project for pre-production testing | 🟠 High | 1 day |
| 4.6 | **Add `flutter test` to CI pipeline** and block merges on failure | 🟠 High | 2 hours |
| 4.7 | **Add `flutter analyze --fatal-infos` to CI** | 🟡 Medium | 30 min |

### Exit Criteria
- [ ] CI pipeline runs: analyze → test → build (Android APK)
- [ ] All edge functions deployed and responding
- [ ] Staging environment mirrors production schema

